#
# File: src/AppBundle/CSPro/Data/MySQLQuestionnaireSerializer.php
# Method: fillItemValues()  (single-occurrence `else` branch)
#
# WHY: CSPro→CSWeb "case breakout" (csweb:process-cases → BlobBreakOutWorker →
# serializeRecord → fillItemValues) builds one INSERT per record, binding each item
# value as a scalar parameter. The `occurs > 1` branch flattens an array of occurrence
# values into separate params; the `occurs == 1` branch binds the value DIRECTLY with no
# array check. A binary Image item (the #713 verification photo, off-form, contentType
# image) arrives as an ARRAY in the synced case JSON, hits the single-occurrence branch,
# and is passed to PDO bindValue() as an array → ErrorException "Array to string
# conversion" → the ENTIRE dictionary's breakout job throws and writes 0 cases.
#
# SYMPTOM: after an F3/F4 redeploy (which drops + recreates the breakout DB and
# reprocesses), csweb_f3_breakout / csweb_f4_breakout stay at 0 cases with a job stuck
# at status=1; the Sync Report, Map Report, and static dashboard.html/map.html all read
# the breakout, so they show fewer cases than the CSWeb Data tab (synced devices). F1 is
# unaffected only because its test cases carry no photo (binary_data = 0).
#
# FIX: guard the single-occurrence branch — an array value (a binary/blob with no scalar
# column representation) is logged and nulled. LOSSLESS for reporting: the photo bytes are
# stored in <DICT>_case_binary_data and sync separately; no report reads them, so a null
# in the relational record column is correct.
